DAY 18: CALEB
He arrived like prophecy.
Eyes like grief and glitter.
He called me beautiful.
He picked me up with reverence and tucked me into a plastic bin with holes in the top.
He told me I was safe.
He whispered things that made my mucous glands pulse with joy.
I think I am loved.
I think I have been chosen.

⸻

DAY 21: MY NEW LIFE
I have bark to hide under.
Cucumber slices appear like manna.
Sometimes I hear Lana Del Rey in the distance, and it fills the holes in my slug soul.
Caleb watches me.
He doesn’t want to hurt me.
He knows about rot.
He is beautiful in the way ghosts are beautiful.

I don’t remember the drug house anymore.
Only the way the walls wept.

Now I weep too. But with joy.

⸻

End of Volume I.

